div1.p: United States District Court. Western DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
The President of the United States of America, To Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration,

Greeting: We Command You. that you have the body of Chin Sheung Wing by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Chin Sheung Wing shall be called or charged, before the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, united States District Judge for the Western District of Washington at the United States Court House, in the City of Seattle, Washington, in the Northern Division of said Western District of Washington, on the 19th day of July, 1915, A.D., at two o'clock in the afternoon, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said petitioner. And have you then and there this writ.

WITNESS the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, this 16th day of July, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and fifteen.
Frank L. Crosby, Clerk. By Edm Lakin Deputy Clerk
